# Unable To Dispose RSA Key before JWT creation.
# General
Hi guys!
Today I updated my project to .NET Core 2.1 and I ran into some issues which I think should be fixed. Basically I have an API that generates JWT tokens igned with RSA. That **was** my code:        
```
using (RSA publicRsa = RSA.Create())
{
            publicRsa.EdoFromXmlString(_options.PublicKey);
            _issuerSigningKey = new RsaSecurityKey(publicRsa);
}
using (RSA privateRsa = RSA.Create())
{
            _privateRsa.EdoFromXmlString(_options.PrivateKey);
            RsaSecurityKey privateKey = new RsaSecurityKey(_privateRsa);
            _signingCredentials = new SigningCredentials(privateKey, SecurityAlgorithms.RsaSha256);
}
_jwtHeader = new JwtHeader(_signingCredentials);
```
Basically, created my RSAs in usings statements, used them and they were auto disposed. Now after upgrading to 2.1 this code was broken and was throwing exceptions on both sides, when creating the JWT and when trying to read it.

I use **Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer** and that's how I create the token. 

```
JwtSecurityTokenHandler _jwtSecurityTokenHandler = new JwtSecurityTokenHandler();
_jwtSecurityTokenHandler.WriteToken(new JwtSecurityToken(_jwtHeader, payload));
```
I use the _jwtHeader generated above and the payload is not that important. 

That is the exeption:
```
System.ObjectDisposedException: Safe handle has been closed
   at System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef(Boolean& success)
   at System.StubHelpers.StubHelpers.SafeHandleAddRef(SafeHandle pHandle, Boolean& success)
   at Interop.Crypto.RsaSize(SafeRsaHandle rsa)
